		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Nice pun, but I already know about Zelda BS. If the makers of the only translated SNES cart that I can afford start making them again, I'll get it, because after playing the ROM a few months ago, I liked what I saw. I want the ORIGINAL FDS sound, Famicom game ( for the Vols glitch, if I can ever get a way to make a Famicom miked controller work on an SNES), and a better translation than the 80's gave us. No offense, because I loved the original NES version, but after playing the Famicom cart, and hearing what the FDS version was like, I believe there could possibly be a BETTER version of the game. I'm calling it Legend Of Zelda: Hyrule Fantasy. Unfortunately, a fantasy might be all it will ever be.

		

