		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: SNES Legend Of Zelda 8 Bit Project</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's quite possible.  Several NES games have been ported to the Turbografx-16 by one person.<br /><br />The SNES is a little more complicated (as the TG-16 is more similar to the NES than the SNES is) but you can do it.<br /><br />You'll need to learn 65816 and SPC-700 assembly.  The SPC program will accept command bytes (ie:pseudo-NES-and-FDS-sound-register-writes) that your conversion program sends it, and will have to emulate the NES and FDS channels.  This is why you'll need SPC assembly in addition to 65816.<br /><br />Sound easy?  Then, get porting!  ;-D

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


